social_posts.post_text: We had to say goodbye to Albus today. He was a good, stubborn dog who brought much joy and love to our lives. We’ll miss you buddy.
Got up to New England this week to see Meemaw. She turned 95 last week and is as sharp as ever.

I spent a great deal of my 20s and 30s convinced that obesity was a lack of willpower, and I’ve come to the conclusion that it simply isn’t. I’ve spent the last six months learning about semaglutides and using them in my fight against obesity and overeating. I’m on day 7 of the injections and writing regularly about my experience on Substack if you want to follow along. Link in bio!
Incredibly proud of Jamie being the featured artist at @armakehub — she’s being recognized for her remarkable talent and creativity. Check her out @studiodust.co she’s the best.
Pretty happy Mother’s Day around here.

Happy Birthday to my wife. One of the funnier things that happened this year: she changed her name to Davis and, as a designer, has always prided herself on her penmanship. When she got a new drivers license, it was her first time signing her new name. She wrote Jamie in her normal signature but  panicked on Davis and wrote it like a first grader. Swipe to see it.

I’ve moved into the phase of life where I post about backyard improvements. Jamie and I have been working on our backyard for the last six months and tonight we hung the lights on the finished project, which included losing three weeks after dropping a 12-foot beam on my foot, breaking it, and spending 14 hours in the hospital.
20-Week pregnancy appointment. Jamie: +8 pounds. Ben: -45 pounds. Baby Davis: 11 oz and strong heartbeat.
Ben (98) vs Jed (97) — I get a stroke or two because he has home course advantage so we’ll call it a victory for yours truly.

Update: six full months of semaglutides and seven full months of pregnancy. Ben -64 pounds, Jamie +almost a whole baby. I’m writing weekly on substack about my experiences on the drug and life in general: the link is in my profile and the readership helps me afford the injections. So huge thanks to anyone who has signed up.
We took maternity pictures and just got them back. Sometime soon, my hair and I are going to need to have an open and honest conversation. Yeesh.

We had a great time and love the results, my hairline notwithstanding.  @allieatkissonimaging did our engagement photos three years ago, our wedding pictures two years ago, and knocked it out of the park again with these. Thanks Allie.
Charlotte May joined us a couple weeks early and she’s pretty perfect — 10/17/2023
